## 3. Scrum Backlog

The following backlog was created using a Scrum-inspired approach to organise and prioritise features required for the system. Each feature was assigned a priority level and included a description and test criteria to ensure it met the project requirements.

| Feature | Priority | Description | Test Criteria |
|--------|--------|------------|--------------|
| User Login | High | Allows users to securely log into the system using session authentication | User can log in and access their dashboard |
| Add Task | High | Enables users to create a new task with relevant details | Task is saved in the database and displayed |
| View Tasks | High | Displays all tasks associated with the user | Tasks appear correctly on tasks page |
| Complete Task | High | Allows users to mark a task as completed | Task moves to completed section |
| Restore Task | Medium | Allows users to move a completed task back to active tasks | Task returns to main task list |
| Delete Task | High | Enables users to permanently remove a task | Task is removed from database |
| Calendar View | Medium | Displays tasks visually based on due dates | Dates with tasks show indicator |
| Due Today Filter | Medium | Shows tasks that are due on the current date | Correct tasks appear for today |
| Navigation System | High | Allows movement between pages (dashboard, tasks, completed) | All links navigate correctly |
| UI Styling | Low | Improves visual appearance and usability of the system | Interface is consistent and readable |

Each feature was developed incrementally and tested during implementation to ensure it met the defined criteria. This backlog supported an iterative development process in line with Agile principles.
